Main article: <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cooley%E2%80%93Tukey=
_FFT_algorithm" title=3D"Cooley=E2=80=93Tukey FFT algorithm">Cooley=E2=80=
=93Tukey FFT algorithm</a></div>
<p>By far the most commonly used FFT is the Cooley=E2=80=93Tukey algorithm.=
 This is a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Divide-and-conquer_algo=
rithm" title=3D"Divide-and-conquer algorithm">divide-and-conquer algorithm<=
/a> that <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recursively" class=3D"mw-=
redirect" title=3D"Recursively">recursively</a> breaks down a DFT of any <a=
 href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Composite_number" title=3D"Composite=
 number">composite</a> size <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-elemen=
t-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=
=3D"display: none;"><math xmlns=3D"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altt=
