s.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-Sorensen_Jones_Heideman_Burrus_1987_1_24-1" class=3D"=
reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fast_Fourier_transform#=
cite_note-Sorensen_Jones_Heideman_Burrus_1987_1-24"><span class=3D"cite-bra=
cket">[</span>24<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Bruun's alg=
orithm (above) is another method that was initially proposed to take advant=
age of real inputs, but it has not proved popular.
</p><p>There are further FFT specializations for the cases of real data tha=
t have <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Even_and_odd_functions" tit=
