gain another factor of roughly two in time and memory and the DFT becomes t=
he <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_cosine_transform" titl=
e=3D"Discrete cosine transform">discrete cosine</a>/<a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_sine_transform" title=3D"Discrete sine transform=
">sine transform(s)</a> (<a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_=
cosine_transform" title=3D"Discrete cosine transform">DCT</a>/<a href=3D"ht=
tps://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Discrete_sine_transform" title=3D"Discrete sine=
 transform">DST</a>).  Instead of directly modifying an FFT algorithm for t=
hese cases, DCTs/DSTs can also be computed via FFTs of real data combined w=
ith <span class=3D"mwe-math-element mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D=
"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y" style=3D"display: none;"><mat=
