<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading3"><h3 id=3D"Accuracy">Accuracy</h3><spa=
n class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">[</span><=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DFast_Fourier_transfo=
rm&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D10" title=3D"Edit section: Accuracy"><sp=
an>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></span></d=
iv>
<p>FFT algorithms have errors when finite-precision floating-point arithmet=
ic is used, but these errors are typically quite small; most FFT algorithms=
, e.g. Cooley=E2=80=93Tukey, have excellent numerical properties as a conse=
quence of the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pairwise_summation" =
title=3D"Pairwise summation">pairwise summation</a> structure of the algori=
thms.  The upper bound on the <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rela=
tive_error" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Relative error">relative error</=
a> for the Cooley=E2=80=93Tukey algorithm is <span class=3D"mwe-math-elemen=
t mwe-math-element-inline"><span class=3D"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-m=
